<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2005-07-13a.152.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100549" speakername="Lord Rooker" colon=":" colnum="152"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds05/text/50713w03.htm#50713w03_spnew0">
	<p pid="a.152.2/1">The per capita cost of a criminal conviction in Northern Ireland in terms of the Police Service of Northern Ireland's budget is set out in the following table.</p>
	<table>
		<tbody>
			<tr pid="a.152.2/4"> <td><i>Financial year</i></td> <td><i>PSNI budget &pound; <sup>1</sup> </i></td> <td><i>Total number of convictions <sup>2</sup> </i></td> <td><i>Per capita cost &pound;</i></td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.152.2/5"> <td>2001&ndash;02</td> <td>641,760,000</td> <td>23,794</td> <td>26,972</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.152.2/6"> <td>2002&ndash;03</td> <td>655,265,000</td> <td>24,596</td> <td>26,641</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.152.2/7"> <td>2003&ndash;04</td> <td>669,770,000</td> <td>N/A</td> <td>&ndash;</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.152.2/8"> <td>2004&ndash;05</td> <td>696,877,000</td> <td>N/A</td> <td>&ndash;</td> </tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<p pid="a.152.2/11">Conviction data beyond 2002&ndash;03 are not yet available.</p>
	<p pid="a.152.2/12">NB</p>
	<p pid="a.152.2/13"><sup>1</sup> Main police grant cash revenue and capital, excluding non-cash items, pensions, Patten severance and non-severance funding.</p>
	<p pid="a.152.2/14"><sup>2</sup> Figures are based on a principal offence rule and include all criminal convictions (coverage excludes convictions stemming from departmental prosecutions, public bodies and private individuals).</p>
</reply>
